Package: vca2-vcass-modules-dkms
Architecture: all
Section: kernel
Priority: optional
Depends:
 ${misc:Depends},
 dkms,
 make,
 gcc,
 linux-headers-generic | linux-headers
Recommends:
 daemon-vca
Provides:
 vcass-modules
Conflicts:
 vcass-modules
Replaces:
 vcass-modules
Description: Intel VCA2 host kernel modules as DKMS source
 This package installs the Intel Visual Compute Accelerator 2 host kernel
 module sources into /usr/src and registers them with DKMS.  It is based on
 Intel VCA 2.3.26 vcass modules with Ubuntu 22.04 / Linux 6.8 compatibility
 fixes, including the BlockIO port.
 .
 The host-side package intentionally blacklists vca_csa because vca_csm owns
 /sys/class/vca on the host.

